Curae is the dative commonly called the predicative dative. This dative is usually a semi-abstract substantive, always in the singular number, and without any attribute, except some- times a simple quantitative adjective, e.9., magnus, minor.- it expresses that which a thing or person serves as or occasions, e.9., puer mihi solacio est, esitio est mare nautis = the boy is a consolation to me, the sea is a source of death to sailors.
